title: Yahoo Lifestyle
text: Scott: “No one has fought harder for working families in the Bronx and Queens than Alexandria. Whether it’s Medicare for All or the Green New Deal, her progressive agenda puts ordinary people first, and is overwhelmingly popular as a result” ~~ But, what has she ACTUALLY done for her constituents? What can she point to and say, “People in my district are better off because of my accomplishments”? Does running 25,000 jobs out of your district help your people? How about all of the jobs that would have supported those 25,000 people (local restaurants & other businesses), are they better off from your decisions? Hopefully, people in her district wise up and realize that she only cares about HER Brand and getting as much time in the media as she can.
